<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" type="diagnosis and remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">Diagnosis and remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">
Type of 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. bispina" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="bispina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. bispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 1949 is destroyed or lost. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I." journalOrPublisher="Scopolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" pagination="1 - 122" refId="B7867379" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P., Shimizu, T., 2008. Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia 64: 1 - 122" title="Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae)" volume="64" year="2008">Sivec et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
place this species in the 
<taxonomicName genus="R." lsidName="R. magnicerca" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" rank="species" species="magnicerca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">R. magnicerca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, based on a series of specimens from Sichuan Province of southwest China. We also collected this species from the type locality and the morphological characteristics of the topotypes we collected agree with the redescription of 
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I." journalOrPublisher="Scopolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735" pagination="1 - 122" refId="B7867379" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P., Shimizu, T., 2008. Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia 64: 1 - 122" title="Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae)" volume="64" year="2008">Sivec et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. The hind area of the head has a lot of spots on hind part (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F8002512" captionText="Figure 13. Rhopalopsole bispina (Wu, 1949). A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711857" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">13</figureCitation>
). Hind border of tergum 9 with a band of knob-like ornamentation, two round sclerotized spots on the anterior margin. Tergum 10 bearing a central plate, the three elements of which are strongly sclerotized. The middle of anterior margin of transverse plates extend backwards with an irregular ornamentation (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F8002512" captionText="Figure 13. Rhopalopsole bispina (Wu, 1949). A Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; B Male terminalia, dorsal view; C Male terminalia, lateral view; D Male terminalia, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e86735.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711857" pageId="0" pageNumber="86735">13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
